&lt;h2&gt;Technician (Endoscopy Decontamination Unit)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can contribute to the excellent patient care at the Queen Alexandra Hospital. We are looking for someone to work as a specialist flexible endoscope technician in the Endoscopy Decontamination Unit, a speciality section of the Hospital Sterilization &amp; Disinfection Unit (HSDU).The main shift work pattern will be 11:00-19:00 M-F but the ideal candidate will be have the flexibility to cover earlier shifts if required, particularly for training.The unit reprocesses flexible endoscopes used in Theatres and Outpatient speciality areas.Handling flexible endoscopes requires someone with good physical stamina and focus to ensure the scope is safely and effectively cleaned, using manual processes and industrial equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 16/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 09/12/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
